y\nAssociation, were given a treat at a\nbanner smoker by their new president,\nJames J. Quigley, last night, it was\nwithout doubt one of the beat affairs\never held by the association. Vaude\nville acts met with satisfaction.\nIf the plans of the chairman, \"Bob\"\nHagen go through, the next smoker\nwhich Will be held In the near future,\nwill Include six boxing bouts. \"Bob\"\nis an intimate friend of \"Bop\" (TBrl\u00e8n\nof Philadelphia, and will endeavor to\nhave some Quaker City talent show\nthc 'r accomplishments before a Wil\n\"\"ngton audience. The Rev. Thomas\nP. Waldron, chaplain of the associa\nHon, and a number of the clergy who\nattended, made speeches.\n'\"\u2022et vP\" fH-D SWEDKfF RECTOR,\nTop Women's Auxiliary of Old\nswedes P. E. Church gave a surprise\nparty last night in honor of the reo\nlor, the Rev, Robert Boll, who has\n'Jp\" 1 the church for five years.\nil, j was Pr\u00ae*\u00aeUt\u00aed with a gold\nwatch and chain by members of the\ncongregation. The presentation vviw\nmade by Mrs. S. F. Swain, anting\npresident of the auxiliary. Mrs. Bell\nwas presented with a set of pearl\nbcads by Mrs. Harold Wilkins.\nWatch the Want Ads for the\nery of lost and found articles.\nrecov\nA.. SCHULTE\n,wvv\\\\\\\\\\xv\\vwtm\\v\\\\\nVNWVWVWUWMOOMSaSc\n200 Cigar Stores and Growing\nThe Biggest Porto Rican Cigar\nValue Ever Offered\n\nI\n\n\noemiine PoiioRican\nCisars\nE8IR|\n\ni\no\n\n\n\nFormerly Priced\n10c and He\n\n\n\nm\n\n\n\ng\ng\nL\ns\ne\nNow\nvK^\n\nA\nC\n5\n\n\u00abo'\n\n,1\nr\n\n\n\ng\n\n\n\n\n\nBox of 50\u2014$2.50\ni|'\n'A*\n\n*8\nCompare these cigars with\nany Porto Rican cigars sell\ning anywhere at 10c or 11c.\nI\u00ab\ng\n\n\n\nV\n\n\nA\n\nMaul Orders FUIed\n\ng\n\n\n\nor post office money order,\ndress our Mail Order Dept.\n217 So. Broad St.\nPhiladelphia\nAd\n\ny\n\ny\ny\ny\ny\n25% Off\ny\n5c size Imported\n'y\ni\nMANILLA LONDRES\n3 For 10c\ny\ny\ny\nAU Our Pipes and\nSmokers' Articles\n\n\ny\ny\n$3.30 Botz of 100\ny\ny\ny\n\n\n10c Size