\nwho committed sutoldc at 18 because\nof the dioulHcs put in the way of\nhis literary aspirations,\nThe lecture was well attended. His\nnext subject will be a contribution of\ntwo lecture\u00ab that were numbered on\nthe program as four and five. They\nare: \"Why First Editions\u2014Association\nBonks\u2014The Bool Beautiful and Biblio\nPoles and Biblto-Phorbs. The lecture\nwill take place on Thursday, Febru\nary 3. at 4 o'clock.\nAn Inch of water on an acre of\nground weighs 100 tons.\nFLAG FOR OGIJCTON SCHOOL.\nMiss Ann Smith, of Newark, has\npresented an American flag to flic\nugleton public school. It was raised\non the tall flagstaff In front of the\nbuilding a day or two ago.\nP\n\nA Safe and Speedy\nRheumatism Remedy\nThat Oilers Two Weeks Treatment\nto Any Sufferer on Money Bark\nPlan\nfnlr to joorHolf. you Fuffor*\u00ab\nrhoumutUm, no matter what form,\nfrom your tlruirirl\u00bbt a package of Khemnt,\nthe guaranteed prescription. Um the en\ntin- bottle, end If you don't think it ha*\ngiven you quick and \u00aballafying relief, tmy\nso. and you can have your money bock.\nIKii't that a fair offer?\nThen utart the Rheuma treatment to\nday. It'\u00ab a reputable physician b prescrip\ntion, altogether different from remedies\nUBiially prescribed\u2014free from narcotics,\nand perfectly harmleM.\nRheuma acts on the kidneys and help\u00ab\nto force the uric acid from the swollen\nJoints and other lodging places. It ahonid\nlease you in a day and make yon hope\n_ol ant\nfunded.\nRheuma has releaaed from Buffering\nrheumatic victims who though nothing\nwould give relief. It should do as much\nfor you\u2014It seldom falls. N. B. Danforth\nwin* Hupply you and guarantee money\nback if not satisfied.\nfrom\nI 1\no\u00abi\nhappy la week or money re-","height":"19320","width":"15756"}}
